== Academic Question

How do different techniques involved in chess programming affect a chess engine's playing strength and efficiency?

== Scope and Limitations

This project focuses on a CPU-based engine using classical search (the alpha-beta family) and both handcrafted and NNUE based evaluation. It does not attempt to reproduce self-play based reinforcement learning systems (like AlphaZero) due to compute requirements. Benchmarks are constrained by available hardware, time controls, and opponent selection.

